quarks.execution

Interface Configs


  • public interface Configs
    Configuration property names. Configuration is passed as a JSON collection of name/value pairs when an executable is submitted.

    The configuration JSON representation is summarized in the following table:

    Summary of configuration properties
    Attribute name Type Description
    JOB_NAME String The name of the job.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static java.lang.String JOB_NAME
      JOB_NAME is used to identify the submission configuration property containing the job name.

    • Field Detail

      • JOB_NAME

        static final java.lang.String JOB_NAME
        JOB_NAME is used to identify the submission configuration property containing the job name. The value is "jobName".
